Windows
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
macOS or Linux
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
Install the official MySQL Connector/Python package:
pip install mysql-connector-python
The official MySQL documentation recommends installing the classic Connector/Python API through the mysql-connector-python package.
Verify the installation:
pip show mysql-connector-python
Test the import:
import mysql.connector

print("MySQL Connector imported successfully.")







Open MySQL Workbench or the MySQL command-line client.
Log in using a MySQL account that has permission to create databases.
Create a Database
